The '''1994 Dubai Open''' was the second edition of this men's [[tennis]] tournament and was played on outdoor [[Tennis courts#Hard courts|hard courts]]. The tournament was part of the [[ATP World Series|World Series]] of the [[1994 ATP Tour]]. It took place in [[Dubai]], [[United Arab Emirates]] from 31 January through 7 February 1994. [[Magnus Gustafsson]] won the singles title.

==Winners==
===Singles===
{{main|1994 Dubai Tennis Championships – Men's Singles}}
{{flagicon|SWE}} '''[[Magnus Gustafsson]]''' defeated {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Sergi Bruguera]], 6–4, 6–2
*It was Gustafsson's second title of the year and the seventh of his career.

===Doubles===
{{main|1994 Dubai Tennis Championships – Men's Doubles}}
{{flagicon|AUS}} '''[[Todd Woodbridge]]''' / {{flagicon|AUS}} '''[[Mark Woodforde]]''' defeated {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Darren Cahill]] / {{flagicon|AUS}} [[John Fitzgerald (tennis)|John Fitzgerald]], 6–7, 6–4, 6–2

