{{Infobox Figure Skating Competition |title= 2006 Austrian Figure Skating Championships |image= |imagesize= |caption= |comptype= National Championships |startdate= 16 December |enddate= 18 December |skatingseason= 2005-2006 |location= [[Innsbruck]] |host= |venue= |prizemoney= |championmen= [[Viktor Pfeifer]] |championladies= [[Andrea Kreuzer]] |championdance= [[Barbora Silná]] / [[Dimitri Matsjuk]] |previouscomp= [[2005 Austrian Figure Skating Championships]] |nextcomp= [[2007 Austrian Figure Skating Championships]] }} The '''2006 Austrian Figure Skating Championships''' ({{lang-de| Österreichischen Staatsmeisterschaften im Eiskunstlauf 2006}}) were the [[Austrian Figure Skating Championships]] of the 2005-2006 [[figure skating season]]. Skaters competed in the disciplines of [[single skating|men's singles, ladies singles]], and [[ice dancing]] for the title of [[list of national championships in figure skating|national champion]] of [[Austria]]. The results of the national championships were used to choose the Austrian teams to the [[2006 Winter Olympic Games]], the [[2006 World Figure Skating Championships]], and the [[2006 European Figure Skating Championships]].
The 2006 Championships took place between 16 December and 18 December 2005 in [[Innsbruck]].
