'''Gwardia Katowice''' is a [[Poland|Polish]] [[sports club]] from [[Upper Silesia]], sponsored by the [[Katowice]] police department. It was founded in 1924 in the [[Second Polish Republic]] under the name '''Policyjny Klub Sportowy Katowice''' (Police Sports Club Katowice) which was changed into the current name after World War II. In the [[Polish culture in the Interbellum|interwar period]] the club was famous for its [[swimmer]]s (numerous champions of Poland) and [[Fencing|fencer]]s. The club adopted its current name Gwardia Katowice in 1949.<ref name="">{{cite journal |title=Z dziejów ruchu sportowego na Śląsku w latach 1945–1989 |trans-title=From the history of sporting movement in Silesia in 1945–1989 |publisher=Instytut Kultury Fizycznej i Turystyki |authors=Teresa i Eligiusz Małolepszy |journal=Kultura Fizyczna. Prace naukowe Akademii im. Jana Dlugosza w Czestochowie |year=2013 |volume=t. XII, nr 1 |at=p. 96 (4 / 18 in PDF) |url=http://dlibra.bg.ajd.czest.pl:8080/Content/1096/Kultura%20fizyczna%2012_01-93.pdf}}</ref>

