The '''Idaho Athletic Hall of Fame''' is a sports [[hall of fame]] in the U.S. state of [[Idaho]]. According to the hall, its purpose is "to honor those individuals from the state of Idaho who have achieved significant recognition in an area of athletic endeavor, or have made a special contribution to Idaho athletics." The 2016 class, inducted in March at the 54th annual North Idaho Sports Banquet, included high school softball coach Larry Bieber, high school basketball coach Sally Greene, football player [[Marvin Washington]], college football assistant coach Bob McCray, and high school track coach Bob Squires.<ref>{{cite news|title=Idaho Athletic Hall of Fame: Bieber Headed For Idaho Hall of Fame|url=http://www.cdapress.com/news/sports/article_afd23461-44ba-5a05-ae50-641640965939.html|accessdate=December 29, 2016|work=Coeur d'Alene Press|date=March 6, 2016}}</ref>

Inducted in 2015 were basketball player [[Orlando Lightfoot]], high school football coach Van Troxel, basketball player Mindy Madsen, and high school sports contributor Bob "Marz" Marzulli.<ref>{{cite news|title=Four will join Idaho Athletic Hall of Fame|url=http://www.spokesman.com/stories/2015/feb/27/four-will-join-idaho-athletic-hall-of-fame/|accessdate=December 29, 2016|work=The Spokesman-Review|date=February 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Four inducted into Idaho Athletic Hall of Fame|url=http://www.nwprepsnow.com/stories/2015/apr/12/four-inducted-into-idaho-athletic-hall-of-fame/|accessdate=December 29, 2016|publisher=NW Preps Now|date=April 12, 2015}}</ref> Six were inducted in the 2014 class: football player [[Merril Hoge]], college football coach [[Keith Gilbertson]], high school football player Mike Cox, football player [[Ryan Phillips (American football)|Ryan Phillips]], James "Doc" Lynn Jr., and high school coach Gary "Big Daddy" Rasmussen.<ref>{{cite news|title=Six inducted into Idaho Athletic Hall of Fame|url=http://www.spokesman.com/stories/2014/apr/13/six-inducted-into-idaho-athletic-hall-of-fame/|accessdate=December 29, 2016|work=The Spokesman-Review|date=April 13, 2014}}</ref>

