{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Dvorana Podmežakla | nickname = | image = | caption = Podmežakla hall during [[EuroBasket 2013]]. | fullname = | location = [[Jesenice, Jesenice|Jesenice]], [[Slovenia]] | coordinates = {{coord|46.4330656|14.050312|display=inline|type:landmark}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1978 | renovated = 1997, 2013 | expanded = 2009–2011 | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = ice | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenant = | seating_capacity = 4,500<ref name="jesenice">[http://www.zsport-jesenice.si/info.php?id=razp&x=2014033 Športna dvorana Podmežakla - II. faza]</ref> | dimensions = 61 x 30 m | scoreboard = }}
'''Podmežakla Hall''' (''Dvorana Podmežakla'') is an [[indoor arena|indoor sporting arena]] located in [[Jesenice, Jesenice|Jesenice]], [[Slovenia]]. It is the home of the [[HDD Jesenice]] [[ice hockey]] team and its affiliate [[HD Hidria Jesenice]].<ref name="eurohockey.com">{{cite web| url=http://www.eurohockey.com/arena/1218-dvorana-podmeakla-jesenice.html |title=Dvorana Podmežakla Jesenice |work=EuroHockey.com |accessdate=2011-03-29}}</ref> It is also the site of the [[Triglav Trophy]], an annual international figure skating competition held each spring.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.slovenia.info/?drugi_sporti=2124&lng=2 |title=Športni park Podmežakla |work=Slovenia.info |publisher=Slovenian Tourist Board |accessdate=2011-03-29 |language=Slovenian}}</ref> The name ''Podmežakla'' (literally 'below Mežakla') is derived from its location on the southwest bank of the [[Sava Dolinka|Sava]] River, directly below the [[Mežakla]] Plateau.
[[File:Slohokej liga HD Mladi Jesenice HDD Bled.webm|thumb|[[HD Mladi Jesenice]] vs. [[HDD Bled]] in the [[2011–12 Slohokej League season]]]]
==History== The hall was opened in 1978 and was expanded between 2009 and 2011.<ref name="jesenice"/> In March 2011, the hall was closed after inspectors determined that the hockey club was allowed to host spectators on the newly built eastern stand without an official state permit for it. The state inspectors also determined that [[Jesenice, Jesenice|Jesenice municipality]] neglected to obtain permit for the new parts built during the last major renovation in 1997.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.dnevnik.si/novice/slovenija/1042430780 |title=Dvorana Podmežakla zaprta zaradi nespametnega odpiranja vzhodne tribune |author=Knez, Primož |date=2011-03-15 |accessdate=2011-03-29 |work=[[Dnevnik (Slovenia)|Dnevnik]] |language=Slovenian}}</ref>
The hall was renovated in 2013 for the [[FIBA EuroBasket 2013]] championship.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.dnevnik.si/sport/kosarka/v-zgornjesavski-dolini-obljubljajo-eurobasket-se-bo-zapisal-v-jesenisko-zgodovino |title=V Zgornjesavski dolini obljubljajo: Eurobasket se bo zapisal v jeseniško zgodovino | date = 14 June 2013 | work = Dnevnik | accessdate = 15 June 2013 | language = Slovenian}} }</ref>
